text:
If you're someone who wants to enjoy the aspects of a tactical FPS game, secure international friendships, or overall have fun, then Counter-Strike 2 is the perfect choice.

In this game, you:
- Engage enemies in some very tactical combat;
- Interact with people from all around the world;
- Have lot of fun.

And to the company behind this game, Valve, I have one simple request. Please, tell us what actually determines one's Trust Factor and make it possible for us to see what our Trust Factor is.

CS2 is a social experiment outing the best drama events known to man;
either your teammates are a order drop off a temu production line or was built in Germany to hunt down peoples whereabouts, 212 hours of absolute rage baiting to the discussion of making some one believe there mothers job is incorrect. 
10/10 Best Fps, Valid Jonny Sins approved

A game forgotten by the developer!
1. Lack of anti-cheat 10 out of 10 farming bots;
2. A simulator about players killing 10 out of 10 farmbots in 360 head shots;
3. The buggy system displays items from the player if you've met him, of course, 10 out of 10 farm bots;
4. The update is equal to the new bug 10 out of 10 phar bots;
5. A wide selection of bots that will rape you 10 out of 10 farm bots.
We have a wonderful simulator game with bots, forget what a team shooter is, it doesn't even smell like it! 100 out of 10 farm bots!

